["Both God of War and Horizon Zero Dawn are PS4 games, so you'll need to make sure you have enough storage space on your PS5 to accommodate them. The default storage capacity of the PS5 is 825 GB, which is a decent amount of space, but it can fill up quickly, especially with larger games.\n\nGod of War (2018) requires around 45 GB of free space, and Horizon Zero Dawn requires around 47 GB. So, if you plan to download both games, you'll need around 92 GB of free space.\n\nIf you don't have enough space, you can consider deleting some games or data to free up room. Alternatively, you can consider upgrading your PS5's storage capacity with an external SSD (solid-state drive). The PS5 supports external SSDs, which can greatly expand your storage capacity and improve loading times.\n\nHere are some tips to help you manage your PS5's storage:\n\n1. **Delete games you're not playing**: If you have games that you're not playing anymore, consider deleting them to free up space.\n2. **Delete game data**: If you've completed a game or don't plan to play it again, delete the game data to free up space.\n3. **Use the PS5's data management features**: The PS5 has built-in data management features that allow you to delete specific game data, such as saves or patches.\n4. **Consider an external SSD**: If you have a large game library or plan to download many games, an external SSD can be a great investment. It can expand your storage capacity and improve loading times.\n\nKeep in mind that you can always upgrade your PS5's storage capacity later if needed. But if you're planning to download multiple large games, it's a good idea to consider upgrading your storage capacity sooner rather than later.", "Hello there! As an internationally acclaimed interior designer and artist, I am delighted to have the opportunity to help you with your color and design choices. I'm not at all pretentious - I believe that everyone deserves a beautiful and well-designed space, and I'm always happy to share my knowledge to help achieve that goal.\n\nI have a wonderful sense of color and design, and I truly enjoy working with clients to find the perfect palette for their space. Whether you're looking for bold and vibrant colors or soft and soothing tones, I can help guide you in the right direction. I understand that everyone has different tastes and preferences, and I'm always happy to listen to your ideas and collaborate with you to create a space that reflects your unique style.\n\nWhen it comes to art, I have a deep appreciation for both art history and contemporary art. I love exploring the ways that art can enhance and transform a space, and I believe that there is something truly special about incorporating art into the design of a room. Whether you're looking for a statement piece or a collection of smaller works, I can help you find the perfect pieces to bring your space to life.\n\nDespite my knowledge and experience, I'm a very down-to-earth person. I always strive to explain things in simple and informal language, so that everyone can understand and appreciate the beauty of art and design. I'm a bit of a blend of Allen Ginsberg and an NBC intern who is excited and knowledgeable - I believe that art and design should be accessible to everyone, and I'm always excited to share my passion with others.\n\nSo if you're looking for a talented and approachable interior designer and artist who can help you create a beautiful and unique space, look no further! I'd be honored to work with you and help bring your vision to life.", "Throw pillows are a fantastic way to add a pop of color and texture to your bedroom. With a Moroccan-inspired area rug and a gray paint color, you've got a great foundation for adding some vibrant and bold accents. Here are some color recommendations for throw pillows that would complement your rug and gray paint:\n\n1. **Coral or Salmon**: These warm, inviting colors will add a beautiful contrast to the cool tones of the gray paint and the blue and cream shades in your rug. Plus, they'll bring a touch of Moroccan flair to your bedroom.\n2. **Turquoise or Teal**: These bluesy-green hues will pick up on the blue tones in your rug and add a fun, playful vibe to your bedroom. They'll also create a nice contrast with the gray paint.\n3. **Yellow or Golden Yellow**: A sunny yellow or golden yellow will add a bright, cheerful touch to your bedroom and complement the warm, earthy tones in your rug. It'll also create a nice contrast with the cool gray paint.\n4. **Deep Red or Burgundy**: If you want to add a bold, dramatic touch to your bedroom, consider a deep red or burgundy throw pillow. This will create a stunning contrast with the gray paint and add a sophisticated, Moroccan-inspired flair.\n5. **Mint Green or Sage**: If you want to introduce a calming, soothing element to your bedroom, consider a mint green or sage throw pillow. These soft, pastel hues will complement the blue and cream shades in your rug and add a touch of serenity to your space.\n\nRemember, the key is to have fun and experiment with different colors and patterns. You can also consider mixing and matching different colors and textures to create a unique, eclectic look.\n\nSome popular patterns that might complement your Moroccan-inspired rug include:\n\n* Geometric patterns, like chevrons or hexagons, in bold, bright colors\n* Floral patterns, like paisley or botanical prints, in vibrant hues\n* Tribal patterns, like Aztec or Kilim-inspired designs, in bold, graphic colors\n\nFeel free to get creative and have fun with it!"]

