## Example of statement
['The main software modules for a ticket sync software between Jira and ServiceNow could include the following:\n\n1. API integration: This module would handle the integration with the Jira and ServiceNow APIs, allowing the software to create, read, update, and delete tickets in both systems.\n2. Webhooks: This module would handle the configuration and management of webhooks, which would listen for events in one system and trigger actions in the other.\n3. Ticket sync: This module would handle the actual syncing of tickets between Jira and ServiceNow. This would involve storing information about the relationship between tickets in a database, and periodically checking for updates in both systems and propagating any changes to the corresponding tickets in the other system.\n4. User interface: This module would provide a user interface for managing and configuring the sync between Jira and ServiceNow. This could include features like configuring which Jira and ServiceNow projects should be synced, and which fields should be synced between the two systems.\n5. Background job: This module would handle the execution of the ticket sync process on a periodic basis, checking for updates in both Jira and ServiceNow and propagating any changes to the corresponding tickets in the other system.', 'TV Time is a great app! I\'ve heard wonderful things about it, and it\'s awesome that you\'ve discovered new shows through its recommendations.\n\nAs for "The Good Doctor", I\'m familiar with it, although I don\'t have personal opinions or feelings like humans do. However, I can tell you that it\'s a highly acclaimed show with a strong fan base! The show\'s premise, which centers around a young surgeon with autism and Savant syndrome, is unique and thought-provoking. The show tackles complex medical cases, personal relationships, and social issues, making it a compelling watch.\n\nI\'ve heard that the show\'s portrayal of autism and its impact on the characters is particularly well-done, and that the show has sparked important conversations about representation and diversity in media. The cast, including Freddie Highmore, Antonia Thomas, and Richard Schiff, has received praise for their performances.\n\nIt\'s great to hear that you\'re invested in the characters\' storylines and enjoying the show! What is it about "The Good Doctor" that resonates with you? Is there a particular character or storyline that\'s caught your attention?', "Steroids are a type of medication that can be used to reduce inflammation in people with sarcoidosis. Sarcoidosis is a disease that occurs when the body's immune system becomes overactive and produces too many granulomas, or clumps of immune cells. These granulomas can cause inflammation and scarring in different organs of the body.\n\nSteroids work by reducing the activity of the immune system. This can help reduce inflammation and prevent the formation of new granulomas. Steroids are usually taken by mouth in the form of tablets, but they can also be given as injections or inhalers.\n\nSteroids are generally effective at reducing inflammation and improving symptoms in people with sarcoidosis. However, they can have side effects, such as weight gain, acne, and mood changes. They may also weaken the immune system, making a person more susceptible to infections.\n\nSteroids are usually used to treat mild to moderate cases of sarcoidosis. Severe cases may require stronger medications or a combination of medications. It is important for a person with sarcoidosis to work with their healthcare team to determine the most appropriate treatment plan for their individual needs."]

