## Example of statement
["Classic and timeless styles are always a great investment, and adding a touch of trendiness can keep your wardrobe fresh and exciting.\n\nThe North Face parka is a great choice, and it's definitely an investment piece. If you're not ready to splurge just yet, waiting for a sale is a great idea. You can also consider looking for similar styles from other brands or last season's models, which might be more affordable.\n\nIt's great to hear that your red sweater has become a staple in your wardrobe! Finding a coat that complements it well will be a great addition to your winter wardrobe. Since your sweater is a bold, bright color, you may want to consider a coat in a neutral color that will provide a nice contrast. Here are a few options to consider:\n\n1. **Neutral colors**: Look for coats in neutral colors like black, navy, gray, beige, or olive green. These colors will provide a nice background for your red sweater and won't compete with it.\n2. **Earth tones**: Earthy colors like brown, tan, or camel can complement the red sweater nicely and add a warm, cozy touch to your outfit.\n3. **Soft pastels**: If you want to add a touch of softness to your outfit, consider a coat in a soft pastel color like pale pink, baby blue, or mint green. These colors will create a nice contrast with the bold red sweater.\n\nWhen trying on coats, make sure to wear your red sweater underneath to get a sense of how the colors work together. You may also want to consider the style of the coat, such as a parka, pea coat, or trench coat, to see which one works best with your sweater.\n\nHow do you feel about shopping during sales or looking for discounts? Do you have a budget in mind for your new coat?", "Here are some additional features that could be included in a comprehensive leave management system:\n\n1. Leave request approvals by proxy: The system should allow managers to delegate leave approval authority to other employees or HR staff, such as in the case of a manager being on leave themselves.\n2. Leave request dependencies: The system should allow employees to specify dependencies when requesting leave, such as requiring the approval of a coworker before taking vacation.\n3. Leave request scheduling conflicts: The system should have a feature that alerts employees and managers when a leave request conflicts with a scheduled shift or project deadline.\n4. Leave request notes: The system should allow employees and managers to add notes to leave requests, such as a reason for the leave or details about coverage during the absence.\n5. Leave request attachments: The system should allow employees and managers to attach documents to leave requests, such as a doctor's note or travel itinerary.\n6. Leave request reminders: The system should send reminders to employees and managers about upcoming or expiring leave requests.\n7. Leave request cancellation: The system should allow employees to cancel leave requests, provided that the request has not yet been approved or the leave has not yet been taken.\n8. Leave request rollover: The system should allow employees to rollover a certain amount of unused leave from one year to the next, provided that the company's leave policies allow it.\n9. Leave request transfer: The system should allow employees to transfer a certain amount of their leave to other employees, provided that the company's leave policies allow it.", "Beauty products can be a significant expense, and finding coupons can definitely help!\n\nI'm glad you were able to save money with the 20% off coupon on the 19th. While I don't have access to specific coupon information or records of past coupon usage, I can offer some general tips to help you find similar coupons for beauty products:\n\n1. **Check beauty brand websites**: Many beauty brands, such as L'Oréal, Maybelline, or Neutrogena, offer printable coupons, digital promotions, or sign-up offers on their websites.\n2. **Sign up for beauty newsletters**: Register for newsletters from your favorite beauty brands to receive exclusive offers, promotions, and early access to new products.\n3. **Look for beauty coupons on coupon websites**: Websites like Coupons.com, CouponCabin, or RetailMeNot often feature beauty product coupons.\n4. **Follow beauty brands on social media**: Many beauty brands offer exclusive promotions, coupon codes, or giveaways on their social media channels.\n5. **Check with beauty retailers**: Visit the websites of beauty retailers like Ulta, Sephora, or Beauty Supply Warehouse to find coupons, promo codes, or loyalty programs that can help you save money.\n6. **Use cashback apps**: Apps like Ibotta, Fetch Rewards, or Checkout 51 sometimes offer rebates or cashback on beauty products.\n7. **Check online deal sites**: Websites like Slickdeals or DealNews aggregate deals and coupons for various products, including beauty items.\n\nRemember to always check the expiration dates and terms of any coupon before using it to ensure it's valid and applicable to your purchase.\n\nKeep in mind that beauty coupons can be less common than those for other products, but it's still worth searching for them. You can also try combining coupons with sales or cashback offers to maximize your savings.\n\nIf you have any more questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!"]

