['With that in mind, I\'d be happy to suggest some local authors from your region who write literary fiction that explores similar themes. Since I\'m a large language model, I don\'t have access to your specific location, but I can provide you with some suggestions on how to find local authors and books that might interest you.\n\n1. **Local Bookstores and Literary Festivals**: Visit local bookstores, especially indie ones, and ask the staff for recommendations. They often have a great knowledge of local authors and can suggest books that fit your preferences. You can also attend literary festivals, author readings, and book launches in your area to discover new authors and network with like-minded readers.\n2. **Online Resources**:\n\t* **Goodreads**: Use Goodreads\' "Explore" feature to find authors from your region. You can filter by location, genre, and rating to discover new authors and books.\n\t* **Local Literary Magazines and Journals**: Look for online literary magazines or journals that feature local authors. These publications often showcase emerging and established writers from your region.\n\t* **Regional Writing Organizations**: Search for writing organizations, guilds, or associations in your area. They often have lists of member authors, publications, and resources.\n3. **Social Media and Book Blogs**: Follow local book bloggers, authors, and literary organizations on social media platforms like Twitter, Instagram, or Facebook. They often share recommendations, reviews, and author interviews that can help you discover new books and authors.\n\nSome examples of literary fiction authors from various regions who explore themes similar to "The Art of Forgetting" are:\n\n* **West Coast, USA**: Authors like Julia Flynn Siler ("The House at the End of the Road"), Laura van den Berg ("Find Me"), or Vendela Vida ("The Diver\'s Clothes Lie Empty") explore themes of identity, memory, and relationships in their works.\n* **East Coast, USA**: Authors like Celeste Ng ("Little Fires Everywhere"), Lauren Acampora ("The Wonder Garden"), or Julia Glass ("A House Among the Trees") delve into similar themes in their novels.\n* **Canada**: Authors like Emily St. John Mandel ("Station Eleven"), Kathryn Kuitenbrouwer ("All the Broken Things"), or Heather O\'Neill ("The Girl Who Was Saturday Night") explore themes of memory, identity, and relationships in their works.\n\nThese are just a few examples, and there are many more authors and books waiting to be discovered. I hope this helps you get started on your literary journey to find more local authors and books that resonate with you!', "As an AI assistant, I couldn't agree more! Transparency is key when it comes to sustainable manufacturing practices and the responsible management of waste. \n\nMany companies, including Reebok, often publish reports on their sustainability and social impact efforts, including their waste management practices. These reports are usually available on the company's website and provide an overview of the company's progress towards its sustainability goals.\n\nMoreover, these reports can detail not only the waste reduction strategies and technologies that the company is using but also the amount of waste it generates, how it is disposed of, and any waste-related incidents or emergencies that have occurred. \n\nBy being transparent about their waste management practices, companies like Reebok can show their commitment to sustainability and demonstrate that they are taking concrete steps to reduce their environmental impact. This transparency can also increase customer trust and loyalty by giving them the information they need to make informed purchasing decisions.", '"When you choose Express Detailers, you\'re choosing a team of professionals with over 20 years of experience in the car detailing industry. We pride ourselves on our active and hands-on approach, ensuring that your car receives the highest level of care and attention. Here are just a few of the benefits you can expect when you hire us:\n\n1. A Professional Team: Our team of skilled technicians are dedicated to providing the highest quality detailing services.\n2. Convenience: With our mobile services, we bring the detailing to you, saving you time and hassle.\n3. Expertise: We have over 20 years of experience in the industry, so you can trust that your car is in good hands.\n4. Affordable: We offer the most affordable mobile detailing service in Orlando, FL.\n5. Quality: We use only the best products and equipment to ensure that your car looks like new when we\'re finished.\n"']

