## Example of statement
['Both Todoist and Trello are popular task management tools, and they offer unique strengths in task prioritization and collaboration. Here\'s a comparison of their features to help you decide which one suits your needs:\n\n**Task Prioritization:**\n\nTodoist:\n\n* Uses a priority system with 4 levels: Priority 1 (high), Priority 2 (medium), Priority 3 (low), and No Priority\n* Allows you to set deadlines and reminders for tasks\n* Offers a "Priority" view that sorts tasks by their priority level\n* Enables you to set a daily goal for completing tasks, which helps you stay focused on high-priority tasks\n* Has a "Priority Matrix" feature that helps you visualize tasks based on their urgency and importance\n\nTrello:\n\n* Uses a Kanban-style board layout, where tasks are organized into lists (e.g., To-Do, In Progress, Done)\n* Allows you to add due dates and deadlines to tasks (cards)\n* Enables you to prioritize tasks by moving them to the top of a list or by using the "Priority" label\n* Offers a "Calendar" view that displays tasks with due dates\n* Has a "Power-Ups" feature that allows you to add custom fields, such as a priority level, to your tasks\n\n**Collaboration Features:**\n\nTodoist:\n\n* Offers real-time commenting and @mentioning team members on tasks\n* Enables task assignment and delegation to team members\n* Has a "Project" feature that allows you to group tasks and share them with team members\n* Offers a "Task Delegation" feature that lets you assign tasks to team members and track their progress\n* Integrates with Google Drive, Slack, and other tools for seamless collaboration\n\nTrello:\n\n* Offers real-time commenting and @mentioning team members on cards\n* Enables card assignment and delegation to team members\n* Has a "Board" feature that allows you to create a visual representation of your project and share it with team members\n* Offers a "List" feature that enables you to create separate lists for different tasks or projects and share them with team members\n* Integrates with Google Drive, Slack, and other tools for seamless collaboration\n* Has a "Power-Ups" feature that allows you to add custom integrations and features to your boards\n\n**Key differences:**\n\n* Todoist is more focused on task management, with a stronger emphasis on prioritization and task delegation. It\'s ideal for individuals or teams who need a more structured approach to task management.\n* Trello is more focused on visual project management, with a Kanban-style board layout that\'s ideal for teams who need to collaborate on complex projects. It\'s more flexible and customizable than Todoist.\n\n**Ultimate decision:**\n\nIf you\'re looking for a task management tool with strong prioritization features and a more structured approach, Todoist might be the better choice. If you prefer a more visual, flexible, and collaborative approach to project management, Trello could be the way to go.\n\nYou might also consider using both tools together: Todoist for task management and Trello for project management. Many users find that using both tools in tandem helps them stay organized and focused.', "Once upon a time, there was a teenager named Jake. Jake had been curious about smoking for a while, but wasn't sure if he should actually try it. One day, while hanging out with some friends, one of them pulled out a pack of cigarettes and offered one to Jake.\n\nDo you want Jake to take the cigarette?\n(yes/no)", '![Image of a person looking at a laptop screen](https://source.unsplash.com/1600x900/?laptop,technology)']

